Van Rompuy Seeks ‘Comprehensive Approach’ on Solving Crisis

-- B y   J a m e s   G .   N e u g e r
-- 
2011-10-17T10:38:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-17/van-rompuy-seeks-comprehensive-approach-on-solving-crisis.html
European Union governments are
preparing a “comprehensive” set of policies to overcome the
debt crisis, EU President  Herman Van Rompuy  said.  Governments are “working on a comprehensive package to
create more confidence in the financial sector and in the
sovereign bonds of countries under pressure,”  Van Rompuy  told
reporters in Brussels today after a meeting with labor and
employer leaders.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James G. Neuger at 
 jneuger@bloomberg.net  